SIMPLE: idler
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Idler
<hw>I"dler</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
idles; one who spends his time in inaction; a lazy person; a
sluggard.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>One who has constant day duties
on board ship, and keeps no regular watch.</def>
<rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>An idle wheel or pulley. See
under <er>Idle</er>.</def></p>

<p><ent>Idlesse</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Idless</ent>⟦br⟧
